# {{ project_name }}

Rust HTTP CloudEvents producer generated by the [xRegistry CLI](https://xregistry.io/) from the `{{ project_name }}` message catalog.

## Layout

- `{{ main_project_name }}/` — the producer crate (`{{ project_name | rust_package }}`).
- `{{ data_project_name }}/` — the generated data-type crate (Serde-serializable structs).

## Usage

```rust
{%- set _mgid = root.messagegroups.keys() | list | first %}
{%- set _mg = root.messagegroups.values() | list | first %}
{%- set _groupname = _mgid | pascal | strip_namespace %}
use {{ project_name | rust_package }}::{{ _groupname }}Producer;

fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    let producer = {{ _groupname }}Producer::new("https://example.com/events")?;
    // producer.send_<message>(data, ...)?;
    Ok(())
}
```

The producer defaults to CloudEvents **structured** content mode. Call
`set_content_mode(ContentMode::Binary)` to switch to HTTP **binary** content mode
(CloudEvents attributes are emitted as `ce-*` headers).

